-- Former HSH Nordbank Bosses Face Hamburg Lawsuits, FAZ Reports
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-01-02T06:43:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-02/former-hsh-nordbank-bosses-face-hamburg-lawsuits-faz-reports.html
Hamburg prosecutors have started
legal proceedings against six previous managers at HSH Nordbank
AG for alleged accounting mistakes,  Frankfurter Allgemeine
Zeitung  reported, without saying where it got the information.  Among the six are former Chief Executive Officers Dirk Jens Nonnenmacher and Hans Berger as well as former management board
members Bernhard Visker and Jochen Friedrich, who all deny the
allegations, the German newspaper reported today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
